        <name>18.4.4.2 Exercise 1</name>
        <questiontext>&lt;p class="HELM_exercise"&gt;Exercise&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The sides of a right-angled triangle enclosing the right-angle are measured as \({@side_1@} \, \textrm{m}\) and \({@side_2@} \, \textrm{m}.\) The maximum errors in each measurement are \(\pm {@max_error@} \, \textrm{m}.\) Find the maximum error in the
    calculated area.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The maximum error is [[input:ans1]] [[validation:ans1]] \(\text{m}^2\).&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Note: Keep 1 s.f. in your answer.&lt;/p&gt;</questiontext>
        <questiontextformat>1</questiontextformat>
        <generalfeedback>&lt;p&gt;The area of a right-angled triangle is \[A=\frac{1}{2}xy\] where \(x, \, y\) are the sides enclosing the right-angle.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;First we calculate \(\dfrac{\partial A}{\partial x}\) and \(\dfrac{\partial A}{\partial y}.\)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;\[ \displaystyle\frac{\partial A}{\partial x} = {@f_x@} \quad \text{and} \quad \displaystyle \frac{\partial A}{\partial y} = {@f_y@} \]&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Therefore, \[\delta A \approx \frac{\partial A}{\partial x} \delta x + \frac{\partial A}{\partial y} \delta y = {@f_x@} \delta x + {@f_y@} \delta y\]&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Letting \(x={@side_1@}, \, y={@side_2@}\) and \( \delta x = \delta y = {@max_error@}\), we obtain \[\delta A \approx \frac{{@side_2@}}{2} \delta x + \frac{{@side_1@}}{2} \delta y = {@(side_2/2)*max_error@}+{@(side_1/2)*max_error@} = {@((side_2/2)*max_error)+((side_1/2)*max_error)@}\text{m}^2.\]&lt;/p&gt;</generalfeedback>
